#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.16:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Gilānavagga"
msgstr "2. Sick"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Tatiyagilānasutta"
msgstr "16. Sick (3rd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.81"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.16:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn46.16:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā ābādhiko hoti dukkhito bāḷhagilāno."
msgstr "Now at that time he was sick, suffering, gravely ill."

msgctxt "sn46.16:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahācundo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ "
"mahācundaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Mahācunda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn46.16:1.4"
msgid "“paṭibhantu taṃ, cunda, bojjhaṅgā”ti."
msgstr "“Cunda, express your understanding of the awakening factors.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.16:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Sattime, bhante, bojjhaṅgā bhagavatā sammadakkhātā bhāvitā bahulīkatā "
"abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the Buddha has rightly explained these seven awakening factors. When "
"developed and cultivated, they lead to direct knowledge, to awakening, and "
"to extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn46.16:2.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "sn46.16:2.3"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo kho, bhante, bhagavatā sammadakkhāto bhāvito bahulīkato "
"abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati … pe … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo kho, "
"bhante, bhagavatā sammadakkhāto bhāvito bahulīkato abhiññāya sambodhāya "
"nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.16:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhante, satta bojjhaṅgā bhagavatā sammadakkhātā bhāvitā bahulīkatā "
"abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the seven awakening factors that the Buddha has rightly explained. "
"When developed and cultivated, they lead to direct knowledge, to awakening, "
"and to extinguishment.”"

msgctxt "sn46.16:2.5"
msgid "“Taggha, cunda, bojjhaṅgā;"
msgstr "“Indeed, Cunda, these are awakening factors!"

msgctxt "sn46.16:2.6"
msgid "taggha, cunda, bojjhaṅgā”ti."
msgstr "Indeed, Cunda, these are awakening factors!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.16:3.1"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā cundo."
msgstr "This is what Cunda said,"

msgctxt "sn46.16:3.2"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "sn46.16:3.3"
msgid "Vuṭṭhahi ca bhagavā tamhā ābādhā."
msgstr "And that’s how the Buddha recovered from that illness."

msgctxt "sn46.16:3.4"
msgid "Tathāpahīno ca bhagavato so ābādho ahosīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.16:3.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
